# Title: Suspicious Svchost Process Access
# Author: Tim Burrell
# Date: 2020-01-02
# Level: high
# Description: Detects suspicious access to the "svchost" process such as that used by Invoke-Phantom to kill the thread of the Windows event logging service.
# MITRE Tactic: Uncategorized
# Tags: attack.defense-impairment, attack.t1685.001
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_access/proc_access_win_svchost_susp_access_request.yml

CallTrace="*UNKNOWN*" GrantedAccess="0x1F3FFF" TargetImage="*:\\Windows\\System32\\svchost.exe" NOT (CallTrace IN ("*Microsoft.Build.ni.dll*", "*System.ni.dll*") SourceImage="*:\\Program Files\\Microsoft Visual Studio\\*" SourceImage="*\\MSBuild\\Current\\Bin\\MSBuild.exe")